venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Venue is wheelchair accessible. Please note it is unlawful for anyone, other than those with a disability or that guest's companion, to use tickets for disabled seating locations (unless such areas have been released for general seating). ** It is encouraged that guests who require accessible accommodations arrive 30 minutes prior to doors opening** Call Box Office for tickets or more information.

generalInfo.generalRule: No bottles, cans, outside food or beverages (including alcohol), any item that can be used as a weapon. No dress code for concerts. ALL SALES ARE FINAL. NO REFUNDS OR EXCHANGES. Camera Policy: Personal cameras are allowed in the venue. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. Lighters are not allowed in the venue and there is absolutely NO SMOKING OR VAPING allowed at the venue per the city of Boston Ordinances. Any smoking or vaping will result in IMMEDIATE EJECTION from the event. All bags larger than 10 in x 9 in, backpacks, professional cameras (i.e detachable lenses), video equipment, luggage, and like articles are strictly prohibited. Please make sure necessary arrangements are made ahead of time as these items are not allowed on the premise. All patrons subject to search upon venue entry. Any medication must be accompanied with proof of prescription. Other prohibited items: drug paraphernalia, weapons, knives, liquid containers, selfie sticks, tablets, laptops, outside food or drinks, any gang affiliated apparel or accessories including bandanas, laser pointers, glass, any LED apparel, candy or beaded jewelry, masks, glow sticks, toys, furry boots, etc.
generalInfo.childRule: No discounts. All ages welcome - unless otherwise stated on the ticket. Everyone needs a ticket for entry.

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: (781) 391-7469 (*this number forwards to the Box Office at The Wilbur when the Chevalier Box Office is not open).
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Chevalier Theatre currently does not have a full-time Box Office. The Box Office will be open 2 hours prior and 1 hour after showtime, day of show only. To buy tickets in advance without service fees please visit the Wilbur Theatre Box Office, located at 246 Tremont St, Boston, MA, 02116. Hours are Monday-Saturday 12-6pm.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, Visa, Mastercard, Discover, American Express
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Location: Box Office (the Box Office is located on the right hand side of the theater) Will Call opens two (2) hours prior to the start of the show and closes (1) hour after the start of the show. Will call tickets can be picked up on the night of the show only. Customers must present a photo I.D. matching the name on ticket account. Tickets may NOT be dropped off or left for other guests.

venues.parkingDetail: From Route 93 (North or South): Medford Square is easily accessed from Route 93. Take Exit 32 for Rt. 60 West. At the rotary, follow the parking attendant who will direct you to the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. From Route 2 (East or West): From Route 2 take Exit 59 and follow the signs for Route 60 East. Stay on Route 60 East through Arlington, and into Medford. Route 60 goes right into Medford Square. When you get to the main intersection in the middle of the square take Riverside Drive to City Hall Mall where you will find the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. There is also plenty of on street paring (Free after 6pm) and municipal parking lots within a few blocks of the theatre.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating policy: The Chevalier Theatre places high priority on the comfort and safety of its patrons. The Chevalier Theatre also recognizes the needs of people with disabilities, as defined by the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) of 1990. Every effort has been made to comply with both ADA and Commonwealth accessibility guidelines to accommodate patrons with disabilities. Accessible seating can be purchased directly via www.ticketmaster.com. Accessible seats will be marked with an ADA icon. For assistance purchasing ADA seats online, please contact Ticketmaster customer service at 800-653-8000. PLEASE NOTE: When a show is over 85% sold any unsold accessible seating will be opened to the general public.

generalInfo.generalRule: Items NOT allowed: NO weapons or firearms, NO cameras, NO recording devices, NO outside food or beverages, NO umbrellas All bags/purses are subject to search upon entry Smoking is NOT permitted. The venue does not permit re-entry. The use of cell phones is strictly prohibited during performances.
generalInfo.childRule: Performances are All Ages unless otherwise noted. Everyone must have a ticket to enter the venue. Parents are encouraged to use reasonable discretion as some concerts/events are not suitable for children.

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Due to the ongoing global pandemic, and to protect the health and safety of our guests and venue staff members, the box office at Oakdale Theatre will be open on-day-of-show only. If you’d like to purchase tickets, please visit us at www.livenation.com. If you’re looking to obtain a refund for a show that was either canceled, postponed or rescheduled, please visit us at www.livenation.com/refund for more information. We look forward to seeing you at our next show at Oakdale Theatre
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, MasterCard, Visa, American Express and Discover cards. Credit cards will only be accepted from the account holder and picture ID is required. NO CHECKS OR SECOND PARTY CREDIT CARDS ARE ACCEPTED.Concessions stands accept cash only..
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will Call is open during regular business hours and on event nights. Any unclaimed Will Call will be brought to the Administrative Offices for latecomers. Picture ID is required for all Will Call. The box office will not accept tickets to be left at Will Call. Please plan accordingly.

venues.parkingDetail: All parking is on site. General parking is included in the price of your ticket. Premier parking is located in the lot closest to the main entrance of the facility for an additional charge and may be purchased in advance at all points of sale. Premier parking may also be purchased just prior to show time at the entrance to the lot. Sales are cash only and are subject to availability. Parking for the disabled is located in the spaces directly in front of the theater for no additional charge and is available to patrons who possess a handicapped parking sticker, hang tag or license plate.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Theater and all facilities are fully ADA accessible. Elevator access to all levels of the facility. Special seating is available for patrons with mobility impairments, visual impairments and hearing impairments. Infra-red hearing devices are available for all shows free of charge (ID required) at the Administrative offices.

generalInfo.generalRule: There is no dress code however shirts and shoes are required. This is a non-smoking facility. A smoking area is located outside of the lobby for attendees. Camera Policy: Personal cameras are allowed in the venue. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. No laser pointers, weapons, large bags. No outside food or beverages are permitted into the facility. Concessions : The theater offers a variety of concessions items. Traditional fare is available at our concessions stands. A full bar is offered as well as beer and wine for adults 21 years and older. Picture ID is required for the purchase of alcoholic beverages. Concessions items are cash only.
generalInfo.childRule: Oakdale Theatre offers a wide variety of programming. Parents and guardians are urged to contact the box office for information on a specific show. For most events, children who have reached their second birthday must have a ticket and occupy their own seat. The availability of discounts for children is also event specific. Please ask at the time of purchase since we are not able to refund all or part of your purchase price. Please visit Oakdale Theatre at www.livenation.com for more information on a specific event.

venues.parkingDetail: From Route 93 (North or South): Medford Square is easily accessed from Route 93. Take Exit 32 for Rt. 60 West. At the rotary, follow the parking attendant who will direct you to the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. From Route 2 (East or West): From Route 2 take Exit 59 and follow the signs for Route 60 East. Stay on Route 60 East through Arlington, and into Medford. Route 60 goes right into Medford Square. When you get to the main intersection in the middle of the square take Riverside Drive to City Hall Mall where you will find the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. There is also plenty of on street paring (Free after 6pm) and municipal parking lots within a few blocks of the theatre.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating policy: The Chevalier Theatre places high priority on the comfort and safety of its patrons. The Chevalier Theatre also recognizes the needs of people with disabilities, as defined by the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) of 1990. Every effort has been made to comply with both ADA and Commonwealth accessibility guidelines to accommodate patrons with disabilities. Accessible seating can be purchased directly via www.ticketmaster.com. Accessible seats will be marked with an ADA icon. For assistance purchasing ADA seats online, please contact Ticketmaster customer service at 800-653-8000. PLEASE NOTE: When a show is over 85% sold any unsold accessible seating will be opened to the general public.

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: (781) 391-7469 (*this number forwards to the Box Office at The Wilbur when the Chevalier Box Office is not open).
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Chevalier Theatre currently does not have a full-time Box Office. The Box Office will be open 2 hours prior and 1 hour after showtime, day of show only. To buy tickets in advance without service fees please visit the Wilbur Theatre Box Office, located at 246 Tremont St, Boston, MA, 02116. Hours are Monday-Saturday 12-6pm.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, Visa, Mastercard, Discover, American Express
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Location: Box Office (the Box Office is located on the right hand side of the theater) Will Call opens two (2) hours prior to the start of the show and closes (1) hour after the start of the show. Will call tickets can be picked up on the night of the show only. Customers must present a photo I.D. matching the name on ticket account. Tickets may NOT be dropped off or left for other guests.

venues.parkingDetail: From Route 93 (North or South): Medford Square is easily accessed from Route 93. Take Exit 32 for Rt. 60 West. At the rotary, follow the parking attendant who will direct you to the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. From Route 2 (East or West): From Route 2 take Exit 59 and follow the signs for Route 60 East. Stay on Route 60 East through Arlington, and into Medford. Route 60 goes right into Medford Square. When you get to the main intersection in the middle of the square take Riverside Drive to City Hall Mall where you will find the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. There is also plenty of on street paring (Free after 6pm) and municipal parking lots within a few blocks of the theatre.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating policy: The Chevalier Theatre places high priority on the comfort and safety of its patrons. The Chevalier Theatre also recognizes the needs of people with disabilities, as defined by the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) of 1990. Every effort has been made to comply with both ADA and Commonwealth accessibility guidelines to accommodate patrons with disabilities. Accessible seating can be purchased directly via www.ticketmaster.com. Accessible seats will be marked with an ADA icon. For assistance purchasing ADA seats online, please contact Ticketmaster customer service at 800-653-8000. PLEASE NOTE: When a show is over 85% sold any unsold accessible seating will be opened to the general public.

generalInfo.generalRule: Items NOT allowed: NO weapons or firearms, NO cameras, NO recording devices, NO outside food or beverages, NO umbrellas All bags/purses are subject to search upon entry Smoking is NOT permitted. The venue does not permit re-entry. The use of cell phones is strictly prohibited during performances.
generalInfo.childRule: Performances are All Ages unless otherwise noted. Everyone must have a ticket to enter the venue. Parents are encouraged to use reasonable discretion as some concerts/events are not suitable for children.

events.info: This is a 21+ Event with valid form of identification. For US citizens, a valid DMV-issued photo ID or USA passport is required. For international guests, a valid passport is required. Doors 10pm All items brought onto the property are subject to inspection. Lighters are not allowed & there is absolutely NO SMOKING OR VAPING allowed at the venue. All bags larger than 10 in x 9 in, backpacks, professional cameras (i.e detachable lenses), video equipment, luggage, & like articles are strictly prohibited. Any medication must be accompanied with proof of prescription. Guests are prohibited from bringing weapons. Weapons include, but are not limited to, the following: firearms, explosives, stun guns, handcuffs, brass knuckles, sticks, clubs, batons, & knives. Patrons with prohibited articles will be turned away at the entrances and no storage or check area will be provided. Violation of the above will result in IMMEDIATE EJECTION.
events.pleaseNote: This is a 21+ Event with valid form of identification. For US citizens, a valid DMV-issued photo ID or USA passport is required. venues.parkingDetail: From Route 93 (North or South): Medford Square is easily accessed from Route 93. Take Exit 32 for Rt. 60 West. At the rotary, follow the parking attendant who will direct you to the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. From Route 2 (East or West): From Route 2 take Exit 59 and follow the signs for Route 60 East. Stay on Route 60 East through Arlington, and into Medford. Route 60 goes right into Medford Square. When you get to the main intersection in the middle of the square take Riverside Drive to City Hall Mall where you will find the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. There is also plenty of on street paring (Free after 6pm) and municipal parking lots within a few blocks of the theatre.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating policy: The Chevalier Theatre places high priority on the comfort and safety of its patrons. The Chevalier Theatre also recognizes the needs of people with disabilities, as defined by the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) of 1990. Every effort has been made to comply with both ADA and Commonwealth accessibility guidelines to accommodate patrons with disabilities. Accessible seating can be purchased directly via www.ticketmaster.com. Accessible seats will be marked with an ADA icon. For assistance purchasing ADA seats online, please contact Ticketmaster customer service at 800-653-8000. PLEASE NOTE: When a show is over 85% sold any unsold accessible seating will be opened to the general public.

venues.parkingDetail: From Route 93 (North or South): Medford Square is easily accessed from Route 93. Take Exit 32 for Rt. 60 West. At the rotary, follow the parking attendant who will direct you to the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. From Route 2 (East or West): From Route 2 take Exit 59 and follow the signs for Route 60 East. Stay on Route 60 East through Arlington, and into Medford. Route 60 goes right into Medford Square. When you get to the main intersection in the middle of the square take Riverside Drive to City Hall Mall where you will find the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. There is also plenty of on street paring (Free after 6pm) and municipal parking lots within a few blocks of the theatre.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating policy: The Chevalier Theatre places high priority on the comfort and safety of its patrons. The Chevalier Theatre also recognizes the needs of people with disabilities, as defined by the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) of 1990. Every effort has been made to comply with both ADA and Commonwealth accessibility guidelines to accommodate patrons with disabilities. Accessible seating can be purchased directly via www.ticketmaster.com. Accessible seats will be marked with an ADA icon. For assistance purchasing ADA seats online, please contact Ticketmaster customer service at 800-653-8000. PLEASE NOTE: When a show is over 85% sold any unsold accessible seating will be opened to the general public.

events.name: Sugar Ray Norcia
events.info: If you love Blues then you'll be excited 3x-GRAMMY® Award Nominee SUGAR RAY NORCIA & THE BLUETONES will be coming to JIMMY'S JAZZ & BLUES CLUB on Wednesday, December 1 at 7:30 P.M. To watch and listen to Sugar Ray & The Bluetones perform at Jimmy's Jazz & Blues Club with our new state-of-the-art production, sound & lighting technologies will be an phenomenal experience!! Jimmy's is the perfect environment to see this acclaimed Blues Band perform!! CHARLIE MUSSELWHITE stated, "Sugar Ray has great tone and phrasing, singing - and playing the harp - One of my favorites." ROCK & BLUES MUSE raved about one of their recent albums, "'Too Far From The Bar' is an all-night bash from end to end and its greatness undeniable. Get all over it and stay there."
events.pleaseNote: 𝟑𝐱-𝐆𝐑𝐀𝐌𝐌𝐘® 𝐀𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐍𝐨𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐞 𝐒𝐔𝐆𝐀𝐑 𝐑𝐀𝐘 𝐍𝐎𝐑𝐂𝐈𝐀 & 𝐓𝐇𝐄 𝐁𝐋𝐔𝐄𝐓𝐎𝐍𝐄𝐒 were nominated for 10 Blues Music Awards in 2017 and 5 Blues Music Awards in 2021, including "Album of the Year" as well as "Band of the Year" and "Traditional Blues - Male Artist of the Year". Norcia himself has 22 Blues Music Award nominations including winning 2 Blues Music Awards in 2014. Norcia has been the driving force behind The Bluetones and he is considered one of this generations most powerful blues vocalists, harmonica players and songwriters. GLIDE MAGAZINE recently declared, "Sugar Ray's vocals have never sounded better..."

events.name: Vincent Ingala
events.info: For all you "Smooth Jazz" fans we are thrilled to announce chart-topping multi-instrumentalist VINCENT INGALA will perform with his Quartet at JIMMY'S JAZZ & BLUES CLUB on Thursday, November 11 at 7:30 PM. His latest effort and seventh studio album, 2021's 'Fire & Desire' finds Vincent playing every instrument throughout the entire album, along with nine original compositions, and the reimagining of Houston Person's dance floor hit, 'Disco Sax.' Ingala feels 'Fire & Desire' is the breath of fresh air that long time smooth jazz fans have been craving. This coast-to-coast sensation continues to bring a playful spirit, old soul, and youthful enthusiasm to contemporary jazz, with a with a real sense for what music fans are seeking, from recordings to live performances. "I believe it is our job as musicians to simply make the music that people enjoy, and hopefully along the way, bring some happiness and inspiration into their lives," shares Vincent, the Prospect, CT native.
events.pleaseNote: 𝐀 𝐁𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐛𝐨𝐚𝐫𝐝 "𝐒𝐦𝐨𝐨𝐭𝐡 𝐉𝐚𝐳𝐳 𝐀𝐫𝐭𝐢𝐬𝐭 𝐨𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐘𝐞𝐚𝐫"- 𝐕𝐈𝐍𝐂𝐄𝐍𝐓 𝐈𝐍𝐆𝐀𝐋𝐀 is a chart-topping multi-instrumentalist with 19 Billboard "Smooth Jazz" Top 10 hits & 6 Billboard "Smooth Jazz" #1 hits. Ingala, who is a Yamaha Performing Artist, has been wowing live audiences with his fun-loving stage presence and an obvious passion for playing. One of the fastest emerging contemporary jazz recording artists in recent history, Ingala burst onto the Contemporary Jazz scene in 2010 with the release of his critically heralded debut album 'North End Soul' and was the Sirius XM Watercolors "Breakthrough Artist Of The Year" in 2013.

events.name: Lindsey Webster
events.info: We are excited to announce Billboard Magazine 2016 & 2017 Artist of the Year LINDSEY WEBSTER will perform at JIMMY'S JAZZ & BLUES CLUB on Saturday November 13 at 7:30 P.M. Webster made history in 2016 with her original, "Fool Me Once", which was the first vocal driven #1 song to top the Billboard Contemporary Jazz chart since Sade's 'Soldier of Love" in 2010. In fact, Webster beat Sade's three week run at number 1 with a four week stay at the top of the charts. In November 2016, Webster made her Shanachie album debut with 'Back To Your Heart', which spawned three songs that reached Top 3 on the Billboard Contemporary Jazz Charts, "Back To Your Heart", "Next To Me" and "Where Do You Want To Go", which hit number 1. In 2018 Webster released the 'Love Inside' album, which featured the Top 5 hit, "Love Inside", and Top 10 single ,"It's Not You, Its Me", featuring Rick Braun.
events.pleaseNote: 𝐁𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐛𝐨𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐌𝐚𝐠𝐚𝐳𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝟐𝐱-𝐀𝐫𝐭𝐢𝐬𝐭 𝐨𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐘𝐞𝐚𝐫 𝐋𝐈𝐍𝐃𝐒𝐄𝐘 𝐖𝐄𝐁𝐒𝐓𝐄𝐑's refreshing approach has garnered two Billboard #1 Hits and seven Top 10 Hits on the Billboard Contemporary Jazz Chart. ALL ABOUT JAZZ hailed the award-winning vocalist and songwriter stating, "Webster is soulful, authentic and belongs on the short list of new talents keeping the tradition alive and taking it to the next level." The chart-topping Webster's flawless vocal range and dynamic ability allows her to perform in a variety of styles from straight-ahead jazz and traditional pop to soulful smooth jazz & adult contemporary and crossover R&B.

events.name: Davina and the Vagabonds
events.info: We are excited to announce the Marvelous, Unique, and truly One-of-a-Kind DAVINA & THE VAGABONDS will perform at JIMMY'S JAZZ & BLUES CLUB on Wednesday, November 24 at 7:30 P.M. Davina & The Vagabonds music consists of a New Orleans sound, featuring elements of blues, jazz, R&B, soul, and gospel!! AMERICAN SONGWRITER stated, "The music, as retro as it may be at times, feels fun, frisky, and alive." DAVINA & THE VAGABONDS shows are filled with New Orleans charm, Memphis soul swagger, dark theatrical moments that evoke Kurt Weill, and tender gospel passages. Davina Sower's voice and stage presence defy category in a different way. Davina has been compared to Etta James, Amy Winehouse, Janis Joplin, and Billie Holiday, but comparisons do not suffice: Sowers is a true original.
events.pleaseNote: 𝐃𝐀𝐕𝐈𝐍𝐀 & 𝐓𝐇𝐄 𝐕𝐀𝐆𝐀𝐁𝐎𝐍𝐃𝐒 have created a stir on the national music scene with their high energy live shows, level A musicianship, sharp dressed professionalism, and Sowers commanding stage presence. With influences ranging from Fats Domino and the Preservation Hall Jazz Band to Aretha Franklin and Tom Waits, the band is converting audiences one show at a time, from Vancouver to Miami and across Europe. ROLLING STONE MAGAZINE hailed Davina Sowers declaring, "Davina Sowers creates her own Americana...a little Amy Winehouse-worthy neo-soul here, a little Great American Songbook-influences songcraft there."

events.name: Brubeck Brothers Quartet
events.info: FULL DINNER SERVICE STARTS TWO HOURS BEFORE SHOWTIME Chris and Dan Brubeck have been making music together practically all their lives. Drummer Dan and bassist, trombonist, and composer Chris cut their first record together in 196 nearly a half century ago. They?ve subsequently played a variety of styles in a number of different groups, as well as with their father, jazz giant Dave Brubeck, and with their own Brubeck Brothers Quartet. With Dan and Chris as the foundation, guitarist Mike DeMicco and pianist Chuck Lamb, complete this dynamic quartet. They perform at concert series, colleges, and jazz festivals across North America and Europe including the Newport, Detroit, Montreal, Playboy/Hollywood Bowl, and Monterey Jazz Festivals. The Quartet?s last cd, LifeTimes was a hit on the Jazz Week radio chart where it made the Top Ten list as one of the most played jazz recordings of the year.

events.name: Material World
events.info: Covering New England presents: MATERIAL WORLD Material World formed in 2018 with a simple goal: form a high energy band to play Madonnas best known and best-loved songs, and then dress it up with a stellar collection of lead singers and a full dance team all to deliver an incredible experience of sing-alongs, dancing, and fun! Not an uninspired tribute act in the traditional sense, but still a highly detailed and faithful re-creation of Madonnas music of the 1980s (nothing after 1990!) only the best of the best. Featuring an eight-piece line-up, plus dancers, Material World boasts an impressive collection of indie rock and punk rock stalwarts (including members of Mr. T Experience, Varsity Drag, Petty Morals, Pansy Division, The Rationales, The Fatal Flaw and more) who are also members of long running Boston area tribute/cover bands Power of Love (Huey Lewis and the News), Heart Attack Ack Ack Ack Ack Ack (Billy Joel) and Bikini Whale (The B-52

events.name: Paul Nelson
events.info: For all you lovers of Blues Music we are excited to announce GRAMMY® Award-Winner Master Blues Guitarist Paul Nelson will be performing with his band on FRIDAY NOVEMBER 12 at 7:30 PM. Paul not only has the distinction of being the hand picked fellow guitarist to the legendary rock/blues icon Johnny Winter in the 2000's, but he has toured the world over performing and or recorded along side top artists...from Eric Clapton and Buddy Guy to Slash, Billy Gibbons, Paul McCartney, Bootsy Collins, Ben Harper, Robben Ford, Vince Gill, Warren Haynes, Derek Trucks, James Cotton, Susan Tedeschi, Kenny Wayne Shepherd, Dr. John, Larry Carlton, Leslie West, Joe Bonamassa, Sonny Landreth, Dickey Betts to Joe Walsh and more. Paul is also a recipient of the Blues Foundation's KBA "Keeping The Blues Alive Award".
events.pleaseNote: 𝐆𝐑𝐀𝐌𝐌𝐘® 𝐀𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐝-𝐖𝐢𝐧𝐧𝐞𝐫 & 𝐌𝐮𝐥𝐭𝐢-𝐆𝐑𝐀𝐌𝐌𝐘® 𝐍𝐨𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐁𝐥𝐮𝐞𝐬 𝐆𝐮𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐭 & 𝐒𝐨𝐧𝐠𝐰𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐏𝐚𝐮𝐥 𝐍𝐞𝐥𝐬𝐨𝐧 is recognized as one of today's top modern contemporary guitarists, songwriters and sought after record producers. Paul's work performing on and producing Johnny Winter's "Step Back" album resulted in winning "Best Blues Album of the Year."

events.name: The Blind Boys of Alabama
events.info: We are happy to announce 5x Grammy Award Winners Blind Boys of Alabama will grace JIMMYS JAZZ & BLUES CLUB stage on Thursday and Friday December 2 & 3 at 7:30 pm. The Blind Boys of Alabama are not just gospel singers borrowing from old traditions; the group helped to define those traditions in the 20th century and almost single handedly created a new gospel sound for the 21st. Since the original members first sang together as kids in Alabama the band has persevered through seven decades to become one of the most recognized and decorated roots music groups in the world. The Blind Boys live shows are roof raising musical events that appeal to audiences of all cultures, as evidenced by an international itinerary that has taken them to virtually every continent. The Blind Boys of Alabama have attained the highest levels of achievement in a career that spans over 75 years and shows no signs of diminishing.
events.pleaseNote: 𝟓𝐱-𝐆𝐑𝐀𝐌𝐌𝐘® 𝐀𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐝-𝐖𝐢𝐧𝐧𝐞𝐫𝐬 & 𝟏𝟎𝐱-𝐆𝐑𝐀𝐌𝐌𝐘® 𝐀𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐍𝐨𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐁𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐝 𝐁𝐨𝐲𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐀𝐥𝐚𝐛𝐚𝐦𝐚 - who are also the recipients of the Grammy® Lifetime Achievement Award - have the rare distinction of being recognized around the world as both living legends and modern-day innovators.

events.name: The Blind Boys of Alabama
events.info: We are happy to announce 5x-Grammy® Award-Winners Blind Boys of Alabama will grace JIMMY'S JAZZ & BLUES CLUB's stage on Thursday and Friday December 2 & 3 at 7:30 pm. The Blind Boys of Alabama are not just gospel singers borrowing from old traditions; the group helped to define those traditions in the 20th century and almost single-handedly created a new gospel sound for the 21st. Since the original members first sang together as kids in Alabama the band has persevered through seven decades to become one of the most recognized and decorated roots music groups in the world. The Blind Boys' live shows are roof-raising musical events that appeal to audiences of all cultures, as evidenced by an international itinerary that has taken them to virtually every continent. The Blind Boys of Alabama have attained the highest levels of achievement in a career that spans over 75 years and shows no signs of diminishing.

events.name: Brubeck Brothers Quartet
events.info: We are excited to announce on Friday December 10 at 8 PM 8 will feature the Brubeck Brothers Quartet.
events.pleaseNote: Chris and Dan Brubeck have been making music together practically all their lives. Drummer Dan and bassist, trombonist, and composer Chris cut their first record together in 196 nearly a half century ago. They?ve subsequently played a variety of styles in a number of different groups, as well as with their father, jazz giant Dave Brubeck, and with their own Brubeck Brothers Quartet. With Dan and Chris as the foundation, guitarist Mike DeMicco and pianist Chuck Lamb, complete this dynamic quartet. They perform at concert series, colleges, and jazz festivals across North America and Europe including the Newport, Detroit, Montreal, Playboy/Hollywood Bowl, and Monterey Jazz Festivals. The Quartet?s last cd, LifeTimes was a hit on the Jazz Week radio chart where it made the Top Ten list as one of the most played jazz recordings of the year.

events.name: Up Close & Personal Chamber Music Series PSO-- String Quartet Tasting
events.info: The Up Close and Personal with the PSO @ Jimmy's Chamber Music Series explores the borderlands between jazz and classical music. Paired with fine food including appetizer, dinner and dessert, this six-concert series promises chamber music like you've never experienced it before. Each performance will feature ensembles of Portsmouth Symphony musicians who will showcase the richness, flexibility, and often surprising range of the classical chamber music repertoire in Jimmy's century-old, spectacularly restored, state-of-the-art club. "The String Quartet Tasting Menu" kicks off the series with a selection of the near endless variety of extraordinary musical flavors, colors and sounds of the string quartet repertoire. Dvorak, Schubert, Haydn, Ravel, Still and myriad other composers wrote some of their most profound works of art for the string quartet. Tonight, you will get a hearty sampling.
events.pleaseNote: https://www.portsmouthsymphony.org/event/2021-22/up-close-and-personal-with-the-pso-chamber-players-jimmys/string-quartet-tasting-menu/

events.name: Jane Monheit
events.info: We are excited to announce 2x-GRAMMY® Nominated Vocalist JANE MONHEIT will be performing at JIMMY'S JAZZ & BLUES CLUB on Thursday November 18 at 7:30 pm. Jane's new album is a tribute to Ella Fitzgerald and we cannot wait to hear exceptional ELLA FITZGERALD SONGS at Jimmy's - with Jane's beautiful and expressive voice behind them - supported by our new state-of-the-art production, sound & lighting technologies. This will be a perfect evening at Jimmy's Jazz & Blues Club!! DOWNBEAT MAGAZINE had this to say, "On her latest album, 'Come What May', Monheit continues to dazzle, delivering a program chockfull of standards, such as "Lush Life", "Let's Face the Music and Dance" and Jobim's "Samba Do Aviro"...on the latter tune ("The Nearness of You"), the combination of Monheit's emotive, wordless flights, and Wayne Haun's lush orchestral arrangement is positively intoxicating."
events.pleaseNote: 𝟐𝐱-𝐆𝐑𝐀𝐌𝐌𝐘® 𝐍𝐨𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐒𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐞𝐫 & 𝐒𝐨𝐧𝐠𝐰𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐉𝐀𝐍𝐄 𝐌𝐎𝐍𝐇𝐄𝐈𝐓 has been one of jazz music's greatest singers over the last 20 years. Blessed with "a voice of phenomenal beauty" (NEW YORK TIMES), Monheit has solidified her status as an impeccable interpreter of the Great American Songbook, combining her love for traditional straight-ahead jazz and the more cinematic songs from theatre and stage. A vocalist with remarkable virtuosity and innate interpretative skills, Monheit puts her own unique touch on every song she sings, establishing herself as one of today's best and most important vocalist-musicians.

events.name: John Pizzarelli
events.pleaseNote: JOHN PIZZARELLI, the world-renowned guitarist and singer, has established himself as a prime contemporary interpreter of the Great American Songbook and beyond, with a repertoire that includes Joni Mitchell, Neil Young, Tom Waits, Antonio Carlos Jobim, and The Beatles. He has been hailed by The Boston Globe for reinvigorating the Great American Songbook and re-popularizing jazz. The Toronto Star pegged him as the genial genius of the guitar. And The Seattle Times saluted him as a rare entertainer of the old school. Following high profile collaborations with Sir Paul McCartney and Michael McDonald, Pizzarelli returns to his roots to honor his hero, the legendary jazz pop vocalist and pianist Nat King Cole, whose centennial is being celebrated around the world this year with various concerts, books and recordings.

events.info: Having recently seen an outstanding show when Warren Wolf recently performed with Christian McBride & Inside Straight at JIMMY'S JAZZ & BLUES CLUB, we are very excited to experience "History of the Vibes" with Warren's outstanding Quartet. To watch and listen to World-Renowned Vibraphonist Warren Wolf and Acclaimed Jazz Pianist & Steinway Artist Helen Sung at JIMMY'S JAZZ & BLUES CLUB on Saturday, November 20 at 7:30 P.M. - supported by our new state-of-the-art production, sound & lighting technologies - will make for an exciting and memorable evening!!

Wolf has been hailed by DOWNBEAT MAGAZINE as "one of the top five vibraphonists in the world." Sung has been praised by JAZZ TIMES, "There is a hierarchy of great piano versions of 'Never Let Me Go', Bill Evans and Keith Jarrett at the top. Sung is now on the list." Archer is one of the most sought-out bassists of his generation.

events.name: Morgan James
events.info: We are excited to announce the Soulful and Passionate Vocalist MORGAN JAMES will be performing at Jimmy's Jazz & Blues Club on Tuesday, November 30 at 7:30 P.M. Let's start with the voice, an instrument through which she can communicate anything!! A gift bestowed upon her that she has expertly trained, meticulously nurtured, and passionately galvanized into action by an urgency to make real music. Next, the stories, and she has them in spades. They are full of truth and beauty, heartache and thoughtfulness. They reveal colors we weren't expecting to see. They make us close our eyes and relate. And finally, the soul - the emotional and intellectual energy through which these parts are fueled. Morgan James is a "soul" singer with that special something - and supported by our new state-of-the-art production, sound, and lighting technologies will make for a very memorable and one-of-a-kind experience at Jimmy's Jazz & Blues Club!!
events.pleaseNote: 𝐒𝐨𝐮𝐥𝐟𝐮𝐥 & 𝐏𝐚𝐬𝐬𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐕𝐨𝐜𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐬𝐭 𝐌𝐎𝐑𝐆𝐀𝐍 𝐉𝐀𝐌𝐄𝐒' authentic and soulful singing prompted the WALL STREET JOURNAL to herald her as "the most promising vocalist to come along this century." The NEW YORK TIMES declared, "Ms. James is a phenomenal talent whose feel for classic soul music is bone deep." BLUES & ROCK MUSE raved about her, "Once in a while you come across a vocalist who is so outstanding, so soulful, that just listening brings chills and a true appreciation for the artist's gift. Morgan James is one such singer and songwriter."

events.name: Popa Chubby
events.info: Over the course of a career that dates back to 1994, he has been a force of to be reckoned with on the guitar, and his tempestuous, soulful playing has never been more powerful. An imposing figure with a shaven head, tattooed arms, a goatee and a performance style he describes as , the Stooges meets Buddy Guy, Motörhead meets Muddy Waters, and Jimi Hendrix meets Robert Johnson. The Blues however was the foundation of his playing style. He recalls, Since I had grown up on Hendrix, Cream and Led Zeppelin, when I started playing blues in New York clubs I understood that the blues should be dangerous, too. It was not just from playing in punk bands. Howlin Wolf and Muddy Waters were dangerous men. They had cut or shoot you if they thought it was necessary, and Little Walter packed a gun and would not hesitate to use it. That danger is a real part of the Blues and I keep it alive in my music.
events.pleaseNote: 𝐏𝐨𝐩𝐚 𝐂𝐡𝐮𝐛𝐛𝐲, 𝐛𝐨𝐫𝐧 𝐓𝐞𝐝 𝐇𝐨𝐫𝐨𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐳, 𝐡𝐚𝐬 𝐛𝐞𝐞𝐧 𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐫𝐨𝐜𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐛𝐥𝐮𝐞𝐬 in his fierce and soulful way for more than 30 years. Over the course of a career that dates back to 1994, he has been a force of to be reckoned with on the guitar, and his tempestuous, soulful playing has never been more powerful. An imposing figure with a shaven head, tattooed arms, a goatee and passionate performance style, Popa Chubby is an endearing character who is one of the genre's most popular figures.

events.name: Emmet Cohen
events.info: Multifaceted American jazz pianist and composer Emmet Cohen is in the vanguard of his generation's advancement of music and the related arts. A recognized prodigy, Cohen began Suzuki method piano instruction at age three, and his playing quickly became a mature melding of musicality, technique, and concept. Downbeat observed that his nimble touch, measured stride and warm harmonic vocabulary indicate he is above any convoluted technical showmanship. Cohen notes that performing jazz is, about communicating the deepest levels of humanity and individuality, it's essentially about connections, both among musicians and with audiences. He leads his namesake ensemble, the Emmet Cohen Trio, is a vibrant solo performer, and is in constant demand as a sideman. Possessing a fluid technique, an innovative tonal palette, and an extensive repertoire, Cohen plays with the command and passion of an artist fully devoted to his medium.
